</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,414,807,829]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">(b) Trochanters pale.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,1173,836,858]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
(c) Sterna (3–) 4–6 with broad posterior margin pale yellow or greenish yellow. … 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Maa" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[1013,1113,836,857]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1013,1113,836,857]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 63
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[151,1008,865,887]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
– (aa) Head color pattern 
<figureCitation box="[432,491,865,887]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-424@40.[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 4. Key to Onycholyda species 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876505/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
