</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,497,895,917]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">(bb) Trochanters mostly black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,1241,924,946]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
(cc) Sterna (3–) 4–6 entirely black, or with very narrow posterior margin pale yellow. … 
<taxonomicName box="[1060,1181,924,945]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1060,1181,924,945]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. yezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 67
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[151,1420,953,1005]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,191,953,975]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">6(2)</emphasis>
(a) Mesoscutellum and metascutellum mostly or entirely black [in Chinese specimens mesoscutellum usually yellow marked]
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,903,1012,1034]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">(b) Wings distinctly yellowish, with veins mostly orange to pale brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,1248,1041,1063]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
(c) Head color pattern as in 
<figureCitation box="[482,541,1041,1063]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-424@40.[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 4. Key to Onycholyda species 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876505/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
: 6c; left mandible bidentate (median tooth absent). … 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Byun" authorityYear="1993" box="[1065,1187,1041,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odaesana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1065,1187,1041,1063]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. odaesana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 65
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[151,657,1071,1093]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">– (aa) Mesoscutellum and metascutellum yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,883,1100,1122]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">(bb) Wings not distinctly yellowish, with veins mostly blackish brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,1432,1129,1151]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
(cc) Head color pattern different (
<figureCitation box="[527,587,1129,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-424@40.[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 4. Key to Onycholyda species 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876505/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
: 7a, b; 8a; 8aa); left mandible tridentate (small median tooth present, 
<figureCitation box="[1255,1314,1129,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-424@40.[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 4. Key to Onycholyda species 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876505/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
: 7a, b). … 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
7 
