<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,220,1239]" box="[199,1422,1188,1210]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
(a) Clypeus entirely black (
<figureCitation box="[468,528,1188,1210]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-424@40.[151,1435,1264,1906]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 4. Key to Onycholyda species 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876505/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
: 7a, b), or with lateral parts and narrow anterior margin brownish. … 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[1198,1362,1188,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroclypeata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1198,1362,1188,1210]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. nigroclypeata</emphasis>
